{"title_page": "Brahma Janen Gopon Kommoti", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 Bengali drama film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Brahma Janen Gopon Kommoti\n| image          = Brahma Janen Gopon Kommoti.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Release poster\n| director       = Aritra Mukherjee\n| producer       = Windows Production\n| writer         = Zinia Sen\n| screenplay     = Zinia Sen\n| starring       = [[Ritabhari Chakraborty]]<br>[[Soham Majumdar]]<br>[[Manasi Sinha]]<br>[[Subhasish Mukherjee]]\n| music          = [[Anindya Chatterjee]]\n| cinematography = Aalok Maiti\n| editing        = Moloy Laha\n| studio         = Windows <br>\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2020|03|06}}\n| country        = India\n| language       = [[Bengali language|Bengali]]\n| Presented by   = Nandita Roy<br> Senco Gold and Diamond\n}}\n\n'''''Brahma Janen Gopon Kommoti''''' is a 2020 Indian [[Bengali language|Bengali]] drama film, directed by Aritra Mukherjee and produced by Windows Production. It stars [[Ritabhari Chakraborty]], Soham Majumdar, Soma Chakraborty, Ambarish Bhattacharya, [[Manasi Sinha]],  and [[Subhasish Mukherjee]]. The story of the film follows Shabari (played by Ritabhari Chakraborty) who is a priest's daughter and a lecturer of Sanskrit. Under influence of  her father's work, she too have a secret desire to perform rituals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/brahma-janen-gopon-kommoti-goes-on-floor/articleshow/72123360.cms|title=\u2018Brahma Janen Gopon Kommoti\u2019 goes on floor - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref>\n\nThe film was released on 6 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/previews/brahma-janen-gopon-kommoti/articleshow/74082207.cms|title=\u2018Brahma Janen Gopon Kommoti'- Times of India|last=|first=|date=|website=The Times of India|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref>\n\n== Synopsis ==\nShabari ([[Ritabhari Chakraborty|Ritabhari]]) is a lecturer and performing artist while simultaneously being in another profession. When she lets her fianc\u00e9 into her multiple identities, he is taken aback and reacts unwelcomingly. This dramatic comedy unwraps the stark differences of our worlds in a combination of outdated rituals, rites, and gender imbalance.\n\n== Cast ==\n\n* [[Ritabhari Chakraborty]] as Shabari\n* [[Manasi Sinha]] as Gurudasi\n* [[Subhasish Mukherjee]] as Purohit Moshai\n* Soham Majumdar as Bikramaditya\n* Soma Chakraborty as Amrabati\n* Ambarish Bhattacharya as Pratapaditya\n\n== Marketing and release ==\nThe first official teaser of the film was released by Windows Production on 10 Jan 2020. The second one was released on 16 Jan 2020. The official trailer of the film was released on 10 February 2020.<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=PPEmuag8FFA|title=BRAHMA JANEN GOPON KOMMOTI OFFICIAL TRAILER - NANDITA- SHIBOPROSAD - RITABHARI - SOHAM - ARITRA|work=Windows|publisher=YouTube|date=10 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nIt was theatrically released on 6 March 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://zeenews.india.com/regional/kabir-singh-actor-in-a-bengali-film-with-a-message-for-women-2263702.html|title='Kabir Singh' actor in a Bengali film with a message for women- Zee News|last=|first=|date=11 February 2020|website=Zee News|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\nRenowned Bengali writer Debarati Mukhopadhyay claimed that the plot of the movie was copied from her book ''Diotima'' without giving any attributions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pycker.com/news/shiboprosad-and-nanditas-brahma-janen-gopon-kommoti-faces-plagiarism-charges/169503828593786|title=Shiboprosad and Nandita's Brahma Janen Gopon Kommoti faces plagiarism charges|website=pyckers|language=en|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref> [[Shiboprosad Mukherjee]] and [[Nandita Roy]] informed that Debarati's claim is baseless and Windows Production filed a suit of 10 crores against Debarati Mukhopadhyay. Smt. Mukhopadhyay also stated that she has filed a counter suit against the production house for plagiarism, copyright violation worth 50 Crores. She also filed a defamation suit against the script writer of the film for humiliating her.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.anandabazar.com/entertainment/controversy-continues-with-brahma-janen-gopon-kommoti-1.1121382|title=\u09a6\u09c7\u09ac\u09be\u09b0\u09a4\u09bf\u09b0 \u09ac\u09bf\u09b0\u09c1\u09a6\u09cd\u09a7\u09c7 \u09e7\u09e6 \u0995\u09cb\u099f\u09bf\u09b0 \u09ae\u09be\u09a8\u09b9\u09be\u09a8\u09bf\u09b0 \u09ae\u09be\u09ae\u09b2\u09be \u09b6\u09bf\u09ac\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09b8\u09be\u09a6\u09a6\u09c7\u09b0, \u09aa\u09be\u09b2\u09cd\u099f\u09be \u09eb\u09e6 \u0995\u09cb\u099f\u09bf\u09b0 \u09ae\u09be\u09ae\u09b2\u09be\u09b0 \u09b9\u09c1\u09ae\u0995\u09bf \u09b2\u09c7\u0996\u09bf\u0995\u09be\u09b0|last=\u09b8\u0982\u09ac\u09be\u09a6\u09a6\u09be\u09a4\u09be|first=\u09a8\u09bf\u099c\u09b8\u09cd\u09ac|website=anandabazar.com|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bengalhour.com/entertainment/copyright-tussle-between-austhor-debarati-mukhopadhayay-and-windows-production-house/|title=Debarati Mukhopadhayay: \u0997\u09b2\u09cd\u09aa \u099a\u09c1\u09b0\u09bf\u09b0 \u0985\u09ad\u09bf\u09af\u09cb\u0997\u09c7 \u09eb\u09e6\u0995\u09cb\u099f\u09bf\u09b0 \u09ae\u09be\u09ae\u09b2\u09be|last=Maitra|first=Somen|date=2020-03-13|website=Bengal Hour|language=en|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Brahma Janen Gopon Kommoti\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Anindya Chatterjee]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 8 March 2020\n| recorded   = 2019\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film Soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]