duction. It stars [[Ritabhari Chakraborty]], Soham Majumdar, Soma Chakraborty, Ambarish Bhattacharya, [[Manasi Sinha]],  and [[Subhasish Mukherjee]]. The story of the film follows Shabari (played by Ritabhari Chakraborty) who is a priest's daughter and a lecturer of Sanskrit. Under influence of  her father's work, she too have a secret desire to perform rituals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/brahma-janen-gopon-kommoti-goes-on-floor/articleshow/72123360.cms|title=\u2018Brahma Janen Gopon Kommoti\u2019 goes on floor - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref>\n\nThe film was released on 6 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/previews/brahma-janen-gopon-kommoti/articleshow/74082207.cms|title=\u2018Brahma Janen Gopon Kommoti'- Times of India|last=|first=|date=|website=The Times of India|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref>\n\n== Synopsis ==\nShabari ([[Ritabhari Chakraborty|Ritabhari]]) is a lecturer and performing artist while simultaneously being in another profession. When she lets her fianc\u00e9 into her multiple identities, he is taken aback and reacts unwelcomingly. This dramatic comedy unwraps the stark differences of our worlds in a combination of outdated rituals, rites, and gender imbalance.\n\n== Cast ==\n\n* [[Ritabhari Chakraborty]] as Shabari\n* [[Manasi Sinha]] as Gurudasi\n* [[Subhasish Mukherjee]] as Purohit Moshai\n* Soham Majumdar as Bikramaditya\n* Soma Chakraborty as Amrabati\n* Ambarish Bhattacharya as Pratapaditya\n\n== Marketing and release ==\nThe first official teaser of the film was released by Windows Production on 10 Jan 2020. The second one was released on 16 Jan 2020. The official trailer of the film was released on 10 February 2020.<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=PPEmuag8FFA|title=BRAHMA JANEN GOPON KOMMOTI OFF